olicies what role does china play amidst international conflicts m taylor fravel is the cecil and ida green career development associate professor of political science and member of the security studies program at mit he studies international relations with a focus on international security china and east asia his current projects examine the evolution of china's military strategy since 1949 and the relationship between material capabilities and political influence in china's rise as a great power downloads audio audio introduction by jean oi talk and q&a session streaming mp3 location philippines conference room encina hall 616 serra st 3rd floor stanford university stanford ca 94305 directions map fsi contact irene bryant topics governance international relations international security and defense china search scp events of interest china's military modernization and national security strategy karl eikenberry china and the world what does china expect from global economic and environmental governance wto g20 imf gmos and climate change in a broader perspective yves tiberghien support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 724 9632 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
